17: Um, hey... I, uh... I had that.
21:
Oh, I'm sorry. Were you actually
planning on delivering the finishing
blow?
23:
You took so long, I thought you were
just here to imbibe the sights.
28:
So why did you call out to me? Was
it to stake some kind of claim on the
treasure? I'm just DYING to hear your
excuses.
33:
What? No, that's not what I was
gonnaâ€”
37:
Life isn't fair, is it? Shame that it
would grace me with so much
talent and you with... none.
41: Now you wait just a minute!
49: Well, I mean... He won't let me SPEAK!
52:
So what? You planning on taking all
the loot?
56:
I would never. I'm nothing if not fair.
So what do you say to half for me,
and half for you?
59:
That's not a bad deal, but... I still
don't like your attitude.
70:
But we haven't divvied up the
treasure yet.
74:
There's no time for that! Come on,
we've gotta move!
82:
*sigh* You'll never get any rest if you
make everyone's business your own.
86: Damn! There's no end to them!
90:
Oh my. Are you having a spot of
trouble?
95:
Obviously, yes! So stop watching
and help out!
99:
I've outgrown playing "warrior of
justice." Besides...
103:
You don't strictly need my help.
You'll claw your way to victory
somehow, won't you? I'll bet you
always do.
108:
So I really don't see what the point of
me leaping in is. We aren't friends,
and there's very little we can offer
each other.
121:
Well, I suppose it never hurts to have
someone in your debt. No matter
how cheap that debt is.
125:
What the? Were you just playing
hard to get or something?
128:
I prefer to keep my prowess a
secret. When people learn you're
strong, they find ways to use you.
132:
...And then there was one. It looks
fairly dangerous. We'll have to tread
carefully...
145: Thank you! You saved our lives!
148:
Don't worry about it. You better get
your injured friends out of here.
150:
Yeah, you're right. First things first
though. It's not much, but I hope
you'll take it as a token of our
appreciation.
153:
Oh, you didn't have to. But we'll
accept the gift anywaysâ€”so as not
to ignore the sentiment behind it.
157: You sure have a way with words...
162:
My name is Adonis. And you... You're
quite the stalwart hero, aren't you?
166:
No, I, uh... wouldn't describe myself
with those words exactly... Hey...
Y-you're kinda close.
169:
I must apologize for my attitude
earlier. I have a bad habit of letting
my pride get the better of me.
171:
And I never imagined you'd be so
strong. I would be honored if you'd
let me into your Kaleidoscope party.
174:
I... I mean... I don't have a problem
with that, but...
178:
You're too kind.
Now, I've got to run, but I look
forward to seeing you again.
182:
Gosh, I, uh... I don't know if it's
because he's so beautiful and
THAT'S throwing me off, but I REALLY
don't know how I feel about him.
184:
No, Alk! Be strong, not shallow! He
was a complete JERK when you first
met.
188:
But maybe I judged him too fast... He
DID offer us half of the treasure...
195:
So they're the new adventurers
everyone's been talking about...
197:
I was worried because no one knew
where they were from, but they're
softer than I expected... I should
have no problem snaking my way
into their good graces.
201:
It'll be the same old game. Keep
your cards close to your chest, and
take all that you can...
